qas.question: Where did the Southeast Asians introduce their dance?
Which dance was famous for strong feet & hand movements?
The Khmer Empire was influenced by what?
Where was dance not popular in Southeast Asia?
Who had a royal ballet in the 700's?
What dance is known for little hand movement?

context: The arts of Southeast Asia have affinity with the arts of other areas. Dance in much of Southeast Asia includes movement of the hands as well as the feet, to express the dance's emotion and meaning of the story that the ballerina is going to tell the audience. Most of Southeast Asia introduced dance <a0_0>into their <b3_0>court<b3_0/><a0_0/>; in particular, <b4_0>Cambodian<b4_0/> royal ballet represented them in the early 7th century before the <b6_0>Khmer Empire,<b6_0/> which was highly influenced by <a2_0>Indian Hinduism<a2_0/>. <a1_0><b5_0>Apsara Dance<b5_0/><a1_0/>, famous for strong hand and feet movement, is a great example of Hindu symbolic dance.
